cs.ET, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CE

The paper discusses optimization problems and the development of a non-combinatorial approach to solving them. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). However, given the focus on optimization problems and the use of self-organizing logic gates, cs.ET and cs.DS seem to be the most likely categories. The use of numerical methods to solve non-linear ordinary differential equations also suggests a potential fit with cs.SY. The paper's potential applications in various fields could also make cs.CE a relevant category.
